					<head>Halakhah</head>
					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85070287" rend="visible">
						<summary>Halakhical works: Tashbets by Samson ben Zadok and Sefer ha-terumah by Baruch ben Isaac.</summary>
						<textLang mainLang="he">Hebrew</textLang>
						<msItem rend="visible" class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85070287">
							<locus from="1r" to="30v"/>
							<title xml:lang="en">Tashbets </title>
							<title n="0" xml:lang="he">תשב"ץ</title>
							<author>
								<persName xml:lang="en" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/8698827">Samson ben Zadok, -1312</persName>
								<persName xml:lang="he" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/8698827">שמשון בן צדוק</persName>
							</author>
							<decoNote>3 initial words decorated with frames inhabited by hybrids in dark brown ink and red.  <locus n="1r, 24r, 24v"/>
							</decoNote>
							<decoNote type="marginal">Decorated paragraph numbers in red.<locus from="1r" to="27v"/>
							</decoNote>
							<decoNote type="marginal">Foliate motifs running vertically at the right sides of the text columns.<locus from="1r" to="27v"/>
							</decoNote>
							<note>
								<p>Folios 28r-30v contain the index.</p>
							</note>
						</msItem>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="31r" to="43v"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Sefer ha-terumah</title>
							<title xml:lang="he">ספר התרומה</title>
							<author>
								<persName xml:lang="en" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/78698989">Baruch ben Isaac, of Worms, active 12th century-13th century</persName>
								<persName xml:lang="he" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/78698989">ברוך בן יצחק, מגרמיזה</persName>
							</author>
							<decoNote type="initial">2 initial words decorated with frames inhabited by hybrids in dark brown and red ink.<locus n="31r, 32v"/>
							</decoNote>
							<decoNote type="marginal">
								<locus from="31r" to="43v"/>Foliate motifs running vertically at the right sides of the text columns.</decoNote>
							<decoNote type="initial">7 initial words decorated with bands filled with foliate motifs in dark brown and red ink.<locus n="36r, 36v, 37v, 38v, 39v, 41r, 42v"/>
							</decoNote>
							<note>
								<p>The arrangement differs a little from both Harley 5648 and the printed editions, and dine ḥalitsah are omitted altogether.</p>
								<p>On folio 43v there is a mezuzah form with biblical rules of writing it, and on folio 44r, the biblical passages used for tefilin are written out in their requisite form.</p>
							</note>
							<filiation>Cf Harley 5648, <ref target="Margoliouth_1965" type="number">518</ref>.</filiation>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Parchment codex of the 14th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="perg">
								<extent>44 folios <dimensions unit="mm" type="leaf">
										<height>305</height>
										<width>210</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>195</height>
										<width>145/150</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>44 folios (+ 1 unfoliated paper flyleaf and 2 new parchment flyleaves at the beginning and at the end).</p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>6 quires: i8 (folio 1-8), ii8 (folio 9-16), iii8 (folio 17-24), iv6 (folio 25-30), v2 (folio 31-32), vi8 (folio 33-40), vi4 (folio 41-44). </p>
									<p>Catchwords at the end of the quires.</p>
								</collation>
								<condition>
									<p>Slightly stained.</p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="3" ruledLines="46" writtenLines="45">
									<p>Uniform layout. </p>
									<p>Visible plummet ruling and pricking.</p>
									<p>Initials written in larger square characters.</p>
									<p>Last line written within the ruling.</p>
									<p>Many marginal notes in semi-cursive and cursive script.</p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc hands="1">
							<summary>Ashkenazi semi-cursive script of the 14th century, unpunctuated. <name type="person" role="scribe">Yehudah ha-Kohen</name>: the words Yehudah and kohen are marked numerous times in the text (e.g. folio 7r, 7v, 8r, 12r, 16v, 26v, 31r, 43r).</summary>
							<handNote script="Hebrew" scope="sole"/>
						</handDesc>
						<additions>
							<p>A formulae of a marriage contract, of a release of claim on a property and of mezuzah (folio 43v), of tefilin (folio 44r), and of a power of attorney (folio 44v). <name type="place">Tinmont </name>
								<date calendar="Hebrew">5067 </date>[<date calendar="Gregorian">1307</date>]: date and origin in the formulae of a marriage contract and of a power of attorney.</p>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="censor">Luigi da Bologna</name>: inscribed with his name: 'Revisto per mi fra Luigi da Bolgona del ordine de Sa' Domenico, Marzo <date calendar="Gregorian">1599</date>' (folio 30v); a converted Jew working for the Inquisition as censor (active at the end of the 16th-beginning of 17th century), see <ref target="Popper_1969" type="page">104</ref>, and appendix § 112-117.
</p>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="censor">Camillo Jaghel</name>: inscribed with his name, <date calendar="Gregorian">1613 </date>(folio 30v); see <ref target="Popper_1969"/>, appendix § 50-56.
</p>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="censor">Renato da Modena</name>: inscribed with his name, <date calendar="Gregorian">1626 </date>(folio 30v); see <ref target="Popper_1969"/>, appendix § 132-133.
</p>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="censor">Fra Gir. Durazzano</name>, active in 1640-41 in Modena-Reggio: inscribed with his name, <date calendar="Gregorian">1640 </date>(folio 30v); see <ref target="Popper_1969"/>, appendix § 89.</p>
						</additions>
						<bindingDesc>
							<binding>
								<p>BM in-house.</p>
								<p>Spine title: ''Works on Halakhah. Hebrew. Brit. Mus. Additional 18,424.'</p>
							</binding>
						</bindingDesc>
